scomm - secure communication
=============================
scomm is a simple end-to-end encrypted communication tool.  You can 
send files and messages to connected peers. Commands are taken from stdin 
and server responses output to stdout.  Errors to stderr.


Commands
----------
To connect to someone else running scomm: ":c <ip of peer>:<port of peer>"

To see active connections: ":i"

To send message: ":m @name1,name2,...,namek Helllllllllllloooooo!"

To send file: ":f @name /path/to/local/file"

To quit: ":q"



Installation
------------
'make' should do it


Running scomm
-----------
Simply invoke the 'scomm' command with the required arguments.